[SN]TITLE[SN]
Newport Road, Cardiff, closed after cyclist crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A cyclist has been involved in a serious crash which has closed one of the main roads into Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The B4487 Newport Road is closed in Rumney after a car and a cyclist collided between Wentloog Road and New Road, near Rumney police station.
South Wales Police is investigating the incident which happened on the westbound carriageway at 07:50 GMT.
Police are warning motorists "to avoid the area" as heavy traffic means delays are expected in the Newport Road area.
